<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="M" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Madness" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Madness,</orth> 1) insanity: <bibl n="shak. son 140.10" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 140, 10</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tmp 2.2.14" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. II, 2, 14</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tmp 5.116.14" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 116</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wiv 4.2.27" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. IV, 2, 27</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mm 4.4.4" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. IV, 4, 4</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mm 5.51.4" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 51</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mm 5.51.4" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 51</bibl> <bibl n="shak. mm 5.51.4" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 51</bibl> <bibl n="shak. err 5.76" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. V, 76</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mv 1.2.69" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. I, 2, 69</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ayl 3.2.420" default="NO" valid="yes">As III, 2, 420</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ayl 4.1.218" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 1, 218</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tn 3.4.16" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. III, 4, 16</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tn 3.4.16" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. III, 4, 16</bibl> <bibl n="shak. tn 4.3.4" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 3, 4</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tn 4.3.4" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 3, 4</bibl> <bibl n="shak. tn 5.302.4" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 302</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wt 4.4.495" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. IV, 4, 495</bibl> etc. etc. <emph>in m.</emph> == mad: <bibl n="shak. ham 3.4.187" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. III, 4, 187</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. oth 1.1.98" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. I, 1, 98</bibl>.<lb />2) extreme folly: <cit><quote>of this m. cured,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h4 4.2.41" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B IV, 2, 41</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>were't not m., to make the fox surveyor of the fold?</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h6 3.1.252" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B III, 1, 252</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>his flight was m.</quote> <bibl n="shak. mac 4.2.2" default="NO" valid="yes">Mcb. IV, 2, 2</bibl></cit>.
<lb />3) wild affection or emotion: <cit><quote>fetter strong m. in a silken thread,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ado 5.1.25" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado V, 1, 25</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>such a hare is m. the youth,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mv 1.2.21" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. I, 2, 21</bibl></cit>.
